In a speech at the American Israel Public Affairs Committee (AIPAC), Vice President Mike Pence addressed the gathering of supporters and emphasized the strong relationship between the United States and Israel. He highlighted President Donald Trump's support for Israel and his actions to strengthen the alliance, such as recognizing Jerusalem as the capital of Israel and withdrawing from the Iran nuclear deal. Pence also condemned anti-Semitism and stated that the US government considers anti-Zionism to be a form of anti-Semitism. He criticized Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders for his criticism of Israel and called for continued support for Trump in order to maintain the strong US-Israel relationship. Pence concluded by expressing optimism for the future of both countries.